All is Cubes 0.3.0
Kevin Reid <kpreid@switchb.org>
Recursive voxel game.

USAGE:
    all-is-cubes [OPTIONS] [FILE]

ARGS:
    <FILE>    Existing save/document file to load. Mutually exclusive with --template. Currently
              supported formats:
              • MagicaVoxel .vox (partial support)

OPTIONS:
        --display-size <W×H>     Window size or image size, if applicable to the selected --graphics
                                 mode. [default: auto]
        --duration <SECONDS>     Time to record video, in 'record' mode only (omit for still image).
    -g, --graphics <MODE>        Graphics/UI mode; one of the following keywords:
                                 • window   — Open a window (uses OpenGL)
                                 • terminal — Colored text in this terminal (uses raytracing)
                                 • headless — Non-interactive; don't draw anything but only
                                 simulates
                                 • record   — Non-interactive; save an image or video (uses
                                 raytracing)
                                 • print    — Non-interactive; print one frame like 'terminal'
                                 mode then exit
                                  [default: window]
    -h, --help                   Print help information
        --no-config-files        Ignore all configuration files, using only defaults and command-
                                 line options.
    -o, --output <FILE>          Output PNG file name for 'record' mode. If animating, a frame
                                 number will be inserted.
        --precompute-light       Fully calculate light before starting the game.
    -t, --template <template>    Which world template to use.
                                 Mutually exclusive with specifying an input file. [default: demo-
                                 city] [possible values: menu, blank, fail, demo-city, dungeon,
                                 atrium, cornell-box, physics-lab, menger-sponge, lighting-bench]
    -v, --verbose                Additional logging to stderr.
    -V, --version                Print version information
